## Regression discovered: invalid marker is not serialized

Finn's closure claim includes "cache/recorded hydration preserves the marker." The hydration code reads `invalid_args_error`, but the committed serialization path drops it: `ToolCall.to_dict()` returns only `id`, `name`, and `args`.

```text
$ nl -ba activegraph/llm/types.py | sed -n '82,96p'
    82	    argument payload.
    83	    """
    84	
    85	    id: str
    86	    name: str
    87	    args: dict[str, Any]
    88	    invalid_args_error: Optional[str] = None
    89	
    90	    def to_dict(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
    91	        return {"id": self.id, "name": self.name, "args": dict(self.args)}
    92	
    93	
    94	@dataclass
    95	class LLMResponse:
    96	    raw_text: str
```

Minimal interpreter-backed reproduction:

```text
$ ../venv/bin/python - <<'PY'
from decimal import Decimal
from activegraph.llm import LLMResponse, ToolCall
from activegraph.llm.cache import _response_from_event_payload
from activegraph.llm.recorded import _response_from_fixture

response = LLMResponse(
    raw_text="",
    parsed=None,
    input_tokens=1,
    output_tokens=1,
    cost_usd=Decimal("0"),
    latency_seconds=0.0,
    model="gpt-4o-mini",
    finish_reason="tool_calls",
    tool_calls=[
        ToolCall(
            id="call_1",
            name="ping",
            args={"_raw": ""},
            invalid_args_error="bad args",
        )
    ],
)
payload = response.to_dict()
cache_hydrated = _response_from_event_payload(payload)
fixture_hydrated = _response_from_fixture(payload, None)
print(payload["tool_calls"][0])
print(cache_hydrated.tool_calls[0].to_dict())
print(fixture_hydrated.tool_calls[0].to_dict())
assert payload["tool_calls"][0]["invalid_args_error"] == "bad args"
assert cache_hydrated.tool_calls[0].invalid_args_error == "bad args"
assert fixture_hydrated.tool_calls[0].invalid_args_error == "bad args"
PY
