## Disposition

Real regression remains against `7a975cd`: invalid OpenAI tool argument markers survive the immediate provider-to-runtime path, but are lost at the durable `LLMResponse.to_dict()` boundary. That means cached or recorded replay can rehydrate the same call without `invalid_args_error`; zero-field schemas can again accept the fallback `{"_raw": ...}` args after replay.

Closure requirement: add a regression test for `invalid_args_error` round-tripping through `LLMResponse.to_dict()` plus cache and recorded hydration, then emit the marker from `ToolCall.to_dict()` when present. This is a regression test closure path, not a contract non-goal, because the implementation already claims and partially implements marker preservation.
